$interpreted: Karen: Never thought that tin can would suspect anything. However, with him, it's likely that he can't tell the real deal from a counterfeit either.
Karen: A Blazetail Lizard crystal, if processed correctly, can be stored for ten years without exploding...
Theodore: So, was the necklace you gifted real, or was it fake?
Karen: From the way Your Majesty is dressed, do you plan to go somewhere far away?
Theodore: Yes. Didn't you say I'm not suited for this desolate desert? So, I plan on leaving.
Karen: Where does Your Majesty plan to go?
Theodore: You'll know when the time is appropriate. I just came to see what decision you made in the end before I set out.
Karen: What about you, Your Majesty? Would you have preferred that I gave her the real necklace or the fake one?
Theodore: It doesn't matter what I preferred. You can't get it back. At the very least, my subordinate is not foolish enough to sacrifice herself for nothing.
Theodore: I'm quite angry at you, actually. For disobeying my orders and taking matters into your own hands. I already have no need for you.
Karen: You...you don't need me anymore?
Theodore: If you can prove yourself useful, perhaps there will be one day where I require your assistance.
Theodore: Then I'll take my leave. Take care of yourself, President of the Chamber of Commerce.
Karen: Well then, now what should I do?
